President Barack Obama has proclaimed May 5, 2015, as National Teacher Appreciation Day and May 3 through May 9, 2015, as National Teacher Appreciation Week. In his proclamation, President Obama highlights the importance of teachers in shaping the lives of children and the future success of the country. He acknowledges the hard work and sacrifices made by teachers and emphasizes the need to provide them with the necessary resources and support to excel in their classrooms. The President also discusses initiatives aimed at promoting excellence in teaching, such as the STEM Master Teacher Corps and the Teach to Lead program. President Obama calls upon students, parents, and all Americans to recognize and support teachers through appropriate activities, events, and programs.